{
  "texts": [
    "Son et al. [208] found that program dependency graphs (PDGs) can represent the structure of code snippets more effectively than ASTs, proposed an enhancement module (PBM) that encodes PDGs as graph embeddings, and designed a framework for implementing PBMs with existing models.",
    "Zhang et al. [209] proposed Re Trans to enhance structural information by adding data flow and control flow edges to the AST and using GCN to encode the entire AST.Huang et al.",
    "[210] explored the feasibility of using bytecode as a source of information to generate code comments.",
    "They used pre-order traversal to serialize the bytecode control flow graph, and combined it with a bytecode token sequence as model input to achieve automatic code summarization in a scenario without available source code.",
    "DatasetsThe following datasets in Table 8 [154,176,182,187,202,211,212] are commonly used for automatic code summarization.TL-CodeSum [202] comprises 69708 method-comment pairs obtained by crawling Java projects developed between 2015 and 2016, each having a minimum of 20 stars on GitHub."
  ]
}